<TITLE> 4 die after mistaking poison for sugar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)Four day labourers died in Sirajganj after consuming what they believed was a packet of sugar on Tuesday, police said. The deceased were identified as Abdullah, 60, Abul Kashem, 16, Farid Uddin, 23, and Bulbuli Khatun, 45, from Digholkandi Gosaibari village in Chouhali upazila. The four died on the spot while another labourer, Rabiul, 40, was taken to hospital after falling ill, Sheikh Abdur Razzaque, police chief of Enayetpur thana, under Chouhali, told bdnews24.com. Razzaque, quoting Rabiul, said that the labourers while working in a field found a polythene packet containing a white substance that looked like sugar. "They ate that with bread at lunch, fell immediately sick and died," said the police officer. "Locals managed to rescue Rabiul in time to send him to the hospital." Police went there after hearing the news, Razzaque added. No doctors could be reached to comment. bdnews24.
